-- Brazilian Stock Movers: Tecnisa, Gol Linhas, Vale Were Active
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-04-16T20:28:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-16/brazil-stock-movers-tecnisa-gol-linhas-aereas-vale-are-active.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index fell 0.2 percent to 61,954.55.  Tecnisa SA (TCSA3)  (TCSA3 BS) gained 0.8 percent to 9.32 reais
after earlier losing as much as 1.6 percent. The homebuilder
said contracted sales fell 54 percent from a year earlier to
253.2 million reais ($137 million).  Gol Linhas Aereas Inteligentes SA (GOLL4)  (GOLL4 BS) fell 2.5
percent to 10.25 reais, a six-month low.  Brazil ’s second-largest
airline said domestic demand declined 10.1 percent in March from
a year earlier, according to a  statement  today.  Vale SA (VALE5)  (VALE5 BS) fell 1.7 percent to 41.24 reais. The
world’s largest iron-ore producer retreated as  metal prices 
reached a three-month low.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zachary Tracer in New York at 
